If I instead use new() to create the instance, references are reported. The same issue arises when with an IEnumerable&lt;T&gt; constructor.  Using the explicit new(values) constructor resolves references while [.. values] does not.

This is annoying when refactoring code since I now have to search for all references to the class to find the constructor usage.

